title.narrative: The national system is strengthened for vulnerable children to access integrated and inclusive social protection services.

description.narrative: Technical assistance provided to NAF contributed to inclusion of 230,000 daily worker in the social protection emergency cash assistance scheme, and around 1,000,000 households in the bread subsidy scheme during the past 4 months, while the UNICEF cash assistance program programs continued its monthly education-labeled cash transfers to cover 11,404 children in vulnerable communities. Additionally, over 128,000 children and parents have been covered by at least one Makani service including 9,000 beneficiaries from marginalized communities. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:27/08/2020
